Members of the Welsh Assembly do not want to “like mappets”
Among some members of the National Assembly, there is dissatisfaction with the proposal to accept the acronym MWP for their name (Member of the Welsh Parliament).
A problematic solution is the plans to change the name of the Assembly to the Welsh Parliament.
Members of the Assembly from different political parties are concerned about possible jokes to this acronym.
One Labourer, expressing his party’s opinion, expressed concern that the new acronym “renames Twp and Pwp.”
For our readers, it's not from Wales: in Welsh twp means "stupid," and pwp means "cushka".
According to a member of the Assembly from the Wales Party, his organization was generally “dissatisfied” and offered other options.
Conservative party representatives do not object to the new acronym, but note that MWP is close to the word Muppet.
In this context, the letter w in Welsh is pronounced roughly as the letter u in the Yorkshire dialect of English.
The Assembly Committee, which is currently drafting a change of name law, made the following statement: “The final decision on the names of the members of the Assembly will, of course, remain with them”.
The Wales Administration Act 2017 has the power to change its name.
In June, the Committee published a public opinion poll on the proposed options, according to which the “Parliament of Wales” option, instead of “Assembly”, was widely accepted by the local population.
With regard to the name of the members of the Assembly, the Committee preferred the option “Welsh Parliament Members” (WMP), while the MWP option received the greatest public support.
Members of the Assembly seem to be offering other options, but it will not be easy for the presiding member, Elin Jones, to find a satisfactory solution; let us remind you that the draft change bill should be submitted in a few weeks.
Reform laws would include other modifications to the Assembly ' s work process, including new rules on disqualification of Assembly members and the establishment of the Committee system.
Members of the Assembly will vote in favour of the final version of their name during the debate on the bill.
